				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I played around with the bolt for awhile, fun fun making the 6k+ crits!
<br />

<br />
But it does suck up the mana.  And as soon as you fire off a bolt, only to have it not count because target died from somebody elses nuke, you lose mana and it's even less effecient. 
<br />

<br />
I just hit 68 and started using Blade Strike (conj. based) as my primary DD now.  With Bolt as the back-up DD, to be used sparingly. 
<br />

<br />
I think with all the Pets, pet toys, <span style="font-weight: bold">mod rods</span>, etc. that conjuration is still the way to go.  Oh, and remember, <span style="font-weight: bold">pet heals</span> are conjuration based.<br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=4796" target="_blank" class="postlink"><span style="font-weight: bold"><span style="color: #FF0000"><span style="font-size: 15px; line-height: normal">Lord Zacatac Soulwanderer</a></span></span></span>
