He said he's using our summoned earring. 15% mana pres on DDs.
<br />

<br />
The real problem is he's assuming a flat 10%. In reality its 1-10% or 5.5% on average. That point is moot though as ornate gloves are 10.5% on average also. 
<br />

<br />
The reason I like SV so much more is that its much less agro, so I can chain nuke early and actually do something rather than having to play the guessing game as to when its safe to lob one off. 
<br />

<br />
Oh, on a totally unrelated note I actually used the lvl 64 anti-summoned spell, Destroy Summoned, for the first time. We were clearing PoA and I got frustrated with the full and partial FR and MR resists I was getting with black steel and SV on the various elemental models. So I loaded up the anti-summoned spell and chain nuked them for full everytime. The cast time is sufficiently fast and the agro so low that I was easily doing 30% more damage than SV. 
<br />

