			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I played around with Itchy's spreadsheet, input my gear numbers, etc.  and used the <span style="text-decoration: underline">summoned earring</span>.
<br />

<br />
Conj. spec 200
<br />
Evoc. spec 50
<br />

<br />
The <span style="text-decoration: underline">Damage per Mana</span> ratios were-
<br />
SV- 7.10
<br />
BoJ- 6.92
<br />
BS- 7.55
<br />

<br />
So blade strike wins the DPM, even when using ornate gloves.  And it is more DPS than SV (but less than BoJ).
<br />

<br />
If I do secondary forte, BoJ moves up to 7.13, still less than BS.   And for me, mana efficiency is fairly critical.  I don't always have every mana buff in life + bard song like the raiders.
<br />

<br />
Of course, if I switched to Evoc, BoJ moves up to 7.64 DPM and beats SV and BS in terms of both DPM and DPS.  But then you lose the other advantages of being conjuration spec.
<br />

<br />
So I guess you have to decide if blasting away with the bolt is the main use of your mana to make it worth switching.<br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=4796" target="_blank" class="postlink"><span style="font-weight: bold"><span style="color: #FF0000"><span style="font-size: 15px; line-height: normal">Lord Zacatac Soulwanderer</a></span></span></span>
<br />
"1450 Club" Tradeskiller</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
