				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody"></span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Aquilistor-Bertoxx wrote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">He said he's using our summoned earring. 15% mana pres on DDs.
<br />

<br />
The real problem is he's assuming a flat 10%. In reality its 1-10% or 5.5% on average. That point is moot though as ornate gloves are 10.5% on average also. </td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
I remember particapating on the mana savings of MP.   We knew it was a random percent with 10 percent being the max.  I stated for a uniform distribution, the average value is the (high range + low range)/2.  We used the high range to be 10 and the low to be 1 to get (10+1)/2 or 5.5% which quickly became the "accepted" answer.     
<br />

<br />
However, random numbers are generated as a range between 0 and 1.  Then multipled to get the needed range and a number is added to get the needed endpoints.  As an example, to get a 1-10 result, you would generate a random number 0-1 and multiple by 9 and add 1 to get a random number from 1 to 10.  
<br />

<br />
I highly doubt EQ generates mana savings as 1-10, but instead is 0-10.  That is a random number (0-1) with the decmial pont shifted.  A very fast thing to program as opposed to the 1-10 number.  I don't know for sure because I have never done the hours of testing required to tell the difference between an average of 5% and an average of 5.5% with EQ's terrible RNG.  But I suspect that MP actually saves 5% and not 5.5%.  
<br />

<br />
I have watched this issue closely and I have never seen anything posted that I thought shows for sure which answer is right.  The 5.5% number seems to have become the accepted answer.  And with the noise of EQ's RNG, it is hard to know which one is right.<br />_________________<br />Dabrighter Blazemeister
<br />
<a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=449337" target="_blank">http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=449337</a></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
