			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Those who keep saying that all nukes should have been conjuration, i just dont get how you think sometimes. The whole idea of specializations was to have choices in order to enhance some of your abilities. Nukes, summons and heals are a different thing. 
<br />

<br />
So for me, summons should have been (and are) conjuration, heals -alteration (no idea why they changed it after 60) and nukes - evocation. You guys all want it to be conjuration, then what's the point of having choices, you just want it all for yourself and spoil the whole idea of specialization.
<br />

<br />
About switching, i say switch now and dont look back. That resist phantasy is only in your minds. In raids dont even think about nuking before malosinia and Hand of Ro is on, in which case i almost never get resists. In grouping mana pres of the lesser nukes are a joke since i never get oom, never - ever.
<br />

<br />
Finally, i am not sure if you all are adding the dps of the critical hits, which enhance the dps a lot considering the bigger base dmg of BoJ. Put Heart of Flame in, even bigger dps. Put the fact that all Time + focus effects (up to lvl 68) invlude BoJ in (lvl 66 spell) and you have the most easy choice which the best results. But the HUGE range of BoJ in, then you can nuke in raids far from all the AE....
<br />

<br />
And who wouldnt want an 8k + nuke (heart of flames) at his disposal all the time? Nuking like a druid just does not do it for me...
<br />

<br />
Vurocan</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
